### `BaseSlider` ŌĆö `src/components/BaseSlider/`
- **Figma**: "Inputs/Slider" ŌĆö two variants: single-thumb (max only) and dual-thumb (range/min-max)
- **Props**: `modelValue?: number` (single, v-model), `minValue?: number` / `maxValue?: number` (range, v-model:minValue / v-model:maxValue), `min?: number` (default 0), `max: number` (**required**), `step?: number` (default 1), `range?: boolean` (default false), `trackMinLabel?: string`, `trackMaxLabel?: string`, `disabled?: boolean`
- **Emits**: `update:modelValue`, `update:minValue`, `update:maxValue`
- **Track**: 4px height, `--color-neutral-80` unfilled, `--color-neutral-20` filled, 11px border-radius. Rendered as a custom div (not the native track) for full cross-browser control.
- **Thumb**: 24├Ś24px solid `--color-neutral-20` circle; `cursor: grab` on hover, `cursor: grabbing` on active; focus ring `box-shadow: 0 0 0 2px --color-accessibility-80`
- **Labels below track**: 14px/22px Roboto Regular `--color-neutral-40`; `8px gap` from track area to labels
- **Parent spacing**: parent should add `16px` gap between the companion label/input row and this component
- **Range fill**: single = `left:0, width: singlePercent%`; range = `left: minPercent%, width: (maxPercent - minPercent)%`
- **Dual-thumb overlap fix**: min input gets `z-index: 3` when `minPercent > 95%` so it remains reachable
- **Usage rules**: always pair with a label + value input above (never standalone); step and range determined per use-case by designer
- **Stories**: SingleDefault, SingleMidValue, SingleAtMax, SingleDisabled, RangeDefault, RangeMidValues, RangeDisabled, InteractiveSingle, InteractiveRange, InteractiveMonthlyPayment, InteractiveDownPayment, BothTypes

