## Token Architecture (White-Label)

The token system has three layers loaded in order:

| Layer | File | Purpose |
|---|---|---|
| **Primitives** | `src/tokens/primitives/echopark.css` | Concrete brand values: color palette + `--font-family-brand` |
| **Semantic** | `src/tokens/semantic.css` | Intent aliases mapping purpose ŌåÆ primitive |
| **Scales** | `src/tokens/tokens.css` | Brand-agnostic: spacing, border, shadow, opacity, typography |

**To white-label for a new brand:** create `primitives/brand-b.css`, redefine the color vars and `--font-family-brand`, then swap the one import line in `main.ts` and `preview.ts`. No component changes needed.

### Semantic token groups
- `--color-action-primary[-hover|-press|-subtle]` ŌĆö primary brand CTA color
- `--color-action-accent[-hover|-press|-subtle]` ŌĆö secondary/link color
- `--color-focus-ring` ŌĆö universal focus indicator
- `--color-surface-disabled`, `--color-text-disabled` ŌĆö disabled state
- `--color-feedback-error[-text|-surface]` ŌĆö error/destructive states
- `--color-feedback-warning[-surface]` ŌĆö caution states
- `--color-feedback-success[-surface]` ŌĆö success/confirmation states
- `--color-feedback-info[-surface]` ŌĆö informational/notification states

### Font family chain
`--font-family-brand` (primitives) ŌåÆ `--font-family-base` (tokens.css) ŌåÆ `--font-family-btn` (tokens.css)

## Design Token Rules
- **Always** use CSS custom properties ŌĆö never hardcode raw color/spacing/radius/typography values
- **In component `<style scoped>` blocks**, use semantic tokens (`--color-action-primary`, `--color-focus-ring`, etc.) for any brand-variable color. Use primitive tokens (`--color-neutral-*`, `--color-neutral-secondary-*`) only for structural neutrals that are unlikely to differ by brand.
- When adding a new token, add to both the appropriate CSS file AND `tokens.ts` simultaneously
- Figma variable defs are the source of truth; screenshot supplements when vars aren't returned
- Old/legacy aliases (`warmgray-*`, `parkgray-70`, `green-50`, `--color-parkgray-0`, `--color-white`) are NOT to be used in components

## Component Rules
- Every component in its own folder: `src/components/ComponentName/`
- Use `<script setup lang="ts">`, `defineProps<{}>()`, `defineEmits<{}>()` ŌĆö no Options API
- `<style scoped>` only ŌĆö no global selectors in component files
- No inline styles unless dynamically computed
- **Reuse first**: before new markup, check whether an existing component (`BaseButton`, `LinkCta`, `Alert`, `Accordion`, etc.) already fits. Do not add hidden one-off primitives inside larger components without explicit sign-off.
- **No new sub-components without checking the user** ŌĆö if a composite needs a new primitive, propose it first.
- **Vue + TypeScript templates**: on **child SFCs**, bind props using the **camelCase name from `defineProps`** (e.g. `ariaLabel`, not `aria-label`). `vue-tsc` treats DOM-style `aria-label` as a separate attribute and will report required props missing.

## Storybook Rules
- Stories co-located in component folder, CSF3 format (`satisfies Meta<typeof Component>`)
- Use `storybook-addon-pseudo-states` for hover/active/focus-visible stories
- a11y is set to `'error'` ŌĆö failing stories must be fixed, not suppressed
- **Top-level sidebar groups**: **`Atoms`**, **`Molecules`**, **`Organisms`**, **`Components`**. Set each storyŌĆÖs `title` on `Meta`; order is controlled in **`.storybook/preview.ts`** via the inline `storySort` comparator (`order` array ŌĆö **must stay inline** for Storybook 10 static analysis; **no TypeScript types inside that function**).
  - **Atoms ŌĆö Buttons / CTAs**: `'Atoms/Buttons/ComponentName'` ŌĆö e.g. `BaseButton`, `LinkCta`, `IconButton`, `TileCta`, `MediumIconButton`, `SmallIconButton`, `ArrowCircleButton`, `VideoControlButton`, `JourneySelector`
  - **Atoms ŌĆö Inputs**: `'Atoms/Inputs/ComponentName'` ŌĆö e.g. `TextBoxSM`, `TextBoxLG`, `TextField`, `BaseSlider`, `BaseRadio`, `BaseCheckbox`, `BaseToggle`, `SegmentedControl`, `SelectDropdown`, `LogicSelector`, `BoxSelector`
  - **Atoms ŌĆö Box inputs (sub-folder)**: `'Atoms/Inputs/Box Input/XS'` (and `/SM`, `/MD`, `/LG`)
  - **Atoms ŌĆö asset galleries** (`src/stories/`): `'Atoms/Icons'`, `'Atoms/Logos'` ŌĆö **no** `Foundations/` parent
  - **Molecules** (flat `Molecules/Name` or sub-folder): `'Molecules/Accordion'`, `'Molecules/Alert'`, `'Molecules/BaseModal'`, `'Molecules/CarOfferInputCard'`, `'Molecules/ContentTile'`, `'Molecules/LocationTile'`, `'Molecules/LocationTileVdp'`, `'Molecules/CarouselDots'`, `'Molecules/FaqBlogTab'`, `'Molecules/ModalTabs'`, `'Molecules/SRPTile'`, plus **`'Molecules/SRP Filters/FilterParent'`**, **`FilterChild`**, **`FilterChildTextLink`**
  - **Organisms** (flat): `'Organisms/GlobalHeader'`, `'Organisms/GlobalFooter'`
  - **Components**: reserved for future page-level / app stories ŌĆö none yet (keep `'Components'` in `preview.ts` `order` if you add some later)

## Figma MCP Workflow
1. **Select node in Figma** (Figma must be open and the desktop app focused)
2. **Generate component**: "generate a Vue component for this" ŌåÆ
   - Call `get_design_context` (clientFrameworks: "vue", clientLanguages: "typescript,css")
   - Call `get_screenshot` immediately after (required)
   - Convert React+Tailwind output ŌåÆ Vue SFC + CSS custom properties
   - Create `ComponentName.vue` + `ComponentName.stories.ts` + `index.ts`
3. **Extract tokens**: "extract tokens from this" ŌåÆ
   - Call `get_variable_defs` + `get_screenshot` simultaneously
   - If screenshot has values not in variable defs, call `get_design_context` for precise values
   - Update `tokens.css` and `tokens.ts`
4. **Single swatch**: Call `get_design_context` ŌĆö exact hex is in `bg-[#xxxxxx]` Tailwind class
5. **Design system rules**: Call `create_design_system_rules` tool ŌåÆ update this rule file

## Naming Conventions
- Components: PascalCase (`BaseButton`, `FormInput`, `NavigationBar`)
- Props: camelCase; emits: camelCase (`"update:modelValue"`, `"click"`, `"dismiss"`)
- CSS custom properties: kebab-case matching Figma variable name pattern (see mapping above)
- Story titles: `'Atoms/ŌĆ”'`, `'Molecules/ŌĆ”'`, `'Organisms/ŌĆ”'`, `'Components/ŌĆ”'` ŌĆö see Storybook Rules and `.storybook/preview.ts` sort order

## Icon & Logo System

### SVG loader setup
- **Plugin**: `vite-svg-loader` (`defaultImport: 'component'`) ŌĆö imported in `vite.config.ts`
- **Aliases**: `@icons/` ŌåÆ `icon/`, `@logos/` ŌåÆ `Logos/`
- **Types**: `src/vite-env.d.ts` declares `*.svg?component` (Vue component), `*.svg?url` (string URL), and `*.svg?raw` (inline SVG string for `v-html` / icons inside styled wrappers)

### System icons (`icon/Style=*.svg`)
- 24├Ś24, single-colour `fill="#242C33"`, always imported with `?component` query
- Filenames: `Style=<Category>, Detail=<Name>, Icon=<Variant>.svg` (original Figma export names, keep as-is)
- **In components that need colour inheritance**: use CSS `:deep()` combinator to override fill:
  ```css
  .my-wrapper :deep(path) { fill: currentColor; }
  ```
- **Gallery story**: `src/stories/Icons.stories.ts` (`Atoms/Icons`)

### Illustrative icons (`icon/Icon=Illustrative, Name=*.svg`)
- Multi-colour, used at larger display sizes ŌĆö do NOT attempt to override colours

### Vehicle Descriptor icons (`icon/Icon Type=Vehicle Descriptors, *.svg`)
- Three size variants: Large (48px), Medium (32px), Small (16px)

### Logos (`Logos/`)
- Always import with `?url` to preserve multi-colour fills: `import epLogo from '@logos/Color=Default.svg?url'`
- Use in `<img src="epLogo" alt="EchoPark" />` ŌĆö NEVER as inline Vue component
- **Gallery story**: `src/stories/Logos.stories.ts` (`Atoms/Logos`)
- Subdirectory `Logos/3rd Party/` contains partner/trust badge logos (same `?url` approach)

## Accessibility
- Semantic HTML first; ARIA only when native semantics are insufficient
- All interactive components need correct roles/attributes
- Storybook a11y addon errors must be resolved before considering a component done
